"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691791","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-27","<p>I can confirm that the Treasury operates a ban the box employment policy in respect of ex-offender job applicants with unspent convictions. Although the Treasury does hold information of unspent convictions, the information requested could only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-02-27T12:45:02.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691791/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691791/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691791/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-02-20","Treasury: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department operates a ban the box employment policy in respect of ex-offender job applicants with unspent convictions; and how many employees of his Department have unspent convictions.","false","Biography information for Andrew Selous","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","64481"
