Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","64672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691950","Department of Health","false","2017-02-23","<p>Figures for the number of families assisted by the Family Nurse Partnership are only held centrally for the past three years. They are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>2015/16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number of families</p></td><td><p>13,212</p></td><td><p>15,789</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The above is national data. Figures by local authority are not held centrally, but can be obtained from the Family Nurse Partnership National Unit at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://fnp.nhs.uk/commission-fnp/national-unit-leadership" target="_blank">http://fnp.nhs.uk/commission-fnp/national-unit-leadership</a></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-23T10:13:42.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691950/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691950/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691950/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","Family Nurse Partnership Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with how many families the family nurse partnership has worked (a) nationally and (b) in each local authority area that it has been in place in each year since that partnership scheme was established.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","64679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691951","Department of Health","false","2017-02-23","<p>This information is not available in the format requested. NHS England publishes data on the performance of ambulance trusts in respect of the number of Category A Red One and Red Two calls responded to within eight minutes and the number of Category A calls resulting in an ambulance arriving at the scene of the incident against the 19 minute standard.</p><p> </p><p>This data is published on a monthly basis at both an England national level and at individual ambulance trust level. Latest data for December 2016 for England and London Ambulance Service NHS Trust is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ambulance-quality-indicators/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ambulance-quality-indicators/</a></p><p> </p><p>Data are not available at regional or London Borough level.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-02-23T14:44:52.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691951/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691951/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691951/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","Ambulance Services: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average NHS ambulance response times in (a) England, (b) Greater London and (c) the London Borough of Newham were in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","64694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691952","Department of Health","false","2017-02-23","<p>There are on-going personal injury claims against the vaccine manufacturer of Pandemrix. We cannot comment whilst these proceedings are on-going.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-23T10:18:15.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691952/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691952/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691952/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","Vaccine Damage Payment Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of compensation available to people who have become disabled as a result of taking the Pandemrix vaccination; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","64695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691953","Department of Health","false","2017-02-28","<p>Through the ‘Stopping Over-Medication of People with Learning Disabilities’ (STOMP) initiative, NHS England and its partners are taking a number of actions to raise awareness and influence the behaviours of professionals in relation to the prescribing of unnecessary antipsychotic or antidepressant drugs.</p><p> </p><p>The Royal Colleges of Psychiatry, Nursing and General Practitioners; Royal Pharmaceutical Society and the British Psychological Society have all undertaken a range of activity in this regard, including audits and the publication of guidance and other materials to promote STOMP to their members.</p><p> </p><p>The Care Quality Commission is undertaking work to equip inspection teams with the awareness, knowledge and tools to assess whether good prescribing practice takes place in services that it regulates.</p><p> </p><p>A STOMP pledge for social care providers and a self-assessment tool will published by the Voluntary Organisations Disability Group during March, with sign up to the pledge expected from across the sector. Additionally, a STOMP pledge is being developed and piloted with healthcare providers, which is expected to be rolled out generally across National Health Service and independent sector providers in summer 2017.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-28T10:26:18.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691953/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691953/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691953/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","Autism and Learning Disability: Prescription Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps are being taken to ensure that NHS staff are aware of the stopping over-medication of people with a learning disability pledge; and what steps are being taken to ensure that people with autism or a learning disability are not prescribed unnecessary antipsychotic or antidepressant drugs.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","64622"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691954","Department of Health","false","2017-02-23","<p>It is important to ensure this strategy is right and Health Education England has made significant progress, working with partners across the mental health system, to develop a costed multi-disciplinary workforce strategy.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-23T10:19:40.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691954/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691954/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691954/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 8 February 2017 to Question 63032, and with reference to the Five Year Forward View for Mental Health of February 2016, what the reason is for the time taken for the publication of the Mental Health Workforce Strategy.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","64641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691955","Department of Health","false","2017-02-28","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence are currently reviewing the evidence for palbociclib in combination with an aromatase inhibitor for treating hormone receptor-positive, human epidermal growth factor receptor 2-negative, locally advanced or metastatic breast cancer in adults. Their draft guidance was out to consultation until 24 February. Stakeholders were encouraged to respond to the consultation.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-28T13:46:03.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691955/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691955/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691955/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","Palbociclib","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the current availability of palbociclib is on the NHS; and what steps are being taken to ensure that all breast cancer patients who would benefit from that drug are able to access it.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","64627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691957","Department of Health","false","2017-02-23","<p>Health Education England has pledged to fund the training of 200 non-medical endoscopists (NMEs) to significantly increase endoscopy capacity in England. The first cohort began training at the end of January 2016 and the second in April 2016 to deliver 40 NMEs. Following a successful evaluation, a further 40 NMEs began training in January 2017.</p><p>The potential impact of the 28 day standard is being tested in five sites; Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust, East Lancashire Hospitals NHS Trust, Kingston Hospital NHS Foundation Trust, Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Ipswich Hospital NHS Trust. Each site is working closely with their clinical commissioning group and NHS England is committed to full implementation of the standard by 2020.</p><p>NHS England recognises the current pressures on endoscopy services and the results of the pilots will inform how the new standard is designed and implemented. NHS England will evaluate the first phase of the project in spring 2017. Alongside this they are developing a new system to collect data to monitor the new standard which they expect to be available from April 2018.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","64458","2017-02-23T16:51:49.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691957/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691957/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691957/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","Cancer: Diagnosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to recommendation 24 of the Independent Cancer Taskforce's report, Achieving World-Class Outcomes, published in May 2016, what progress has been made on implementing the new four-week diagnostic standard for cancer in (a) Peterborough and (b) England since the publication of that report; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Stewart Jackson","Peterborough","Mr Stewart Jackson","64596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691958","Department of Health","false","2017-02-28","<p>Prescribing is a clinical decision made by general practitioners, in line with regulations.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-28T10:27:20.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691958/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691958/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691958/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","Prescription Drugs: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what guidance NHS England provides to GPs on whether GPs can continue to prescribe medication to pensioners in the event that such medication is also available for purchase over the counter.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","64576"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691959","Department of Health","false","2017-02-23","<p>The Vaccine Damage Payment Act 1979 is based on diseases not specific vaccines.</p><p> </p><p>A Vaccine Damage Payment can be considered for those who are severely disabled as a result of a vaccination against those diseases listed in the 1979 Act and those diseases that have been specified since 1979 by statutory instrument. There are no plans to change this.</p><p> </p><p>The list of specified diseases covered by the Act includes Pandemic influenza A (H1N1) swine flu, where vaccination was administered from 10 October 2009 to 31 August 2010.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-23T10:07:38.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691959/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691959/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691959/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","Vaccine Damage Payment Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to amend the Vaccine Damage Payment Act 1979 to make people who have had adverse reactions to the Pandemrix vaccination eligible for the Vaccine Damage Payments Scheme.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","64594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691960","Department of Health","false","2017-02-23","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has advised that a meeting with Pfizer to discuss the appraisal of palbociclib took place on 22 February 2017.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-23T15:05:42.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691960/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691960/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691960/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","Palbociclib","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what meetings representatives from NICE (a) have had and (b) plan to have with Pfizer during the consultation period for palbociclib (Ibrance) since the publication of the draft guidance on that drug on 3 February 2017.","false","Biography information for Sir Simon Burns","Chelmsford","Sir Simon Burns","64599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691961","Department of Health","false","2017-02-23","<p>For the 217 vacant properties held by NHS Property Services (NHSPS):</p><p> </p><p>- The budgeted total cost of maintenance for 2016/17 is £1.5 million; and</p><p>- The budgeted total for other associated costs for 2016/17 is £7.9 million.</p><p> </p><p>This is based on the following assumptions:</p><p> </p><p>- Full-year budgeted expenditure, excluding non-cash items such as depreciation and management fees; and</p><p>- The full-year budgeted figures do not include the savings achieved by disposing of a vacant property part of the way through the year.</p><p> </p><p>The 217 properties constitute 6.9% of the total NHSPS portfolio.</p><p>NHS Property Services is working closely with NHS England and the Department to finalise a ‘Vacant Space Hand Back Scheme’, which is designed to promote efficient use of the health estate and enable commissioners and tenants to save money on their estate costs.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-02-23T17:27:34.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691961/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691961/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691961/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-20","NHS Property Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 9 February 2017 to Question 63167, what the (a) maintenance and (b) other associated costs of the 217 vacant properties held by NHS Property Services are.","true","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr   Poulter","64600"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691962","Home Office","false","2017-02-23","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 7 December 2016 to the question from my hon. Member for Romford, UIN 55575.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-02-23T12:21:26.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691962/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691962/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691962/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-20","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether UK citizens will require new passports after the UK leaves the EU; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","64593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691963","Home Office","false","2017-02-28","<p>The Home Office was informed of G4S’ decision to launch the use of body warn cameras when that decision had been made, and prior to their deployment.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-02-28T15:21:25.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691963/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691963/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691963/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-20","G4S","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 7 February 2017 to Question 62704, whether her Department knew of the G4S decision to use body-worn cameras prior to their pilot and launch.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","64605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691964","Home Office","false","2017-02-27","<p>The number of people leaving detention, by reason is published in tables dt_05 and dt_05_q in ‘Immigration Statistics, July - September 2016’, available from the Home Office website at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/572384/detention-q3-2016-tables.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/572384/detention-q3-2016-tables.ods</a></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-02-27T11:39:31.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691964/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691964/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691964/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-20","Immigrants: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people detained in an immigration removal centre were subsequently removed or deported from the UK in each year from 2013 to 2017.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","64608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691965","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally and could be obtained only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Only main offences are recorded centrally, so offenders may have human trafficking offences as secondary offences which could only be found by examining individual case files.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-28T16:40:46.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691965/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691965/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691965/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people convicted of human trafficking offences in the last three years have been returned to a country of origin (a) within the EU and (b) outside the EU to serve a prison sentence.","false","Biography information for Lord Garnier","Harborough","Sir Edward Garnier","64638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691966","Home Office","false","2017-02-23","<p>The information requested is not recorded on Home Office systems. We do report on the number of decisions made an asylum claims, and, separately, on the number of persons detained for immigration purposes.</p><p>However, we do not have a combined set of data which would allow the question to be answered, and to cross-match these data sets over the period requested (since January 2014) would require a manual data matching exercise.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","64416 ; 64461 ; 64668","2017-02-23T12:19:22.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691966/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691966/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691966/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-20","Children: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many children have been detained by UKVI after submitting an asylum application in each year since 2013.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","64636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691967","Home Office","false","2017-02-27","<p>All changes to the Immigration Rules on work routes are laid before Parliament and guidance is published on <a href="http://www.gov.uk" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a> to explain how migrants will be affected by any revisions to our criteria. We also write to key external partners and stakeholders, including immigration advisors, to communicate the details of any changes being made, where appropriate.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-02-27T10:46:57.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691967/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691967/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691967/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-20","Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department takes to publicise any changes to migrants' rights to work in the UK to people specifically affected by those changes.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","64683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691968","Home Office","false","2017-02-23","<p>The information requested is not recorded on Home Office systems. We do report on the number of decisions made an asylum claims, and, separately, on the number of persons detained for immigration purposes.</p><p>However, we do not have a combined set of data which would allow the question to be answered, and to cross-match these data sets over the period requested (since January 2014) would require a manual data matching exercise.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","64416 ; 64461 ; 64636","2017-02-23T12:19:22.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691968/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691968/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/691968/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-20","Asylum: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many asylum applicants have been detained in each year since 2013, and how many of those applicants were detained in (a) a short-term facility, and (b) an Immigration Removal Centre.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","64668"
