"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692006","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-03","<p>All Ministry of Justice employees are required to complete a mandatory Equality and Diversity training module which makes specific reference to mental health conditions and supporting vulnerable customers. In addition, Mental Health Awareness courses have also been delivered to employees across the country and frontline court training materials also link into the ‘Every Witness Matters’ handbook to ensure that employees are aware of the potential impact that a mental health condition may have on a court user. Colleagues working in National Business Centres have been provided with specific training on ‘Dealing with Traumatic Calls’.</p><p> </p><p>Under the Constitutional Reform Act 2005, responsibility for the training of the judiciary rests with the Lord Chief Justice as Head of the Judiciary. Training on mental health issues is limited to awareness in order to help judges ensure that all court users are treated equally and fairly. Judges are able to access advice and guidance on this through the Equal Treatment Bench Book which is publicly available at: <a href="https://www.judiciary.gov.uk/publications/equal-treatment-bench-book/" target="_blank">https://www.judiciary.gov.uk/publications/equal-treatment-bench-book/</a></p><p> </p><p>Data relating specifically to the effectiveness of the training is not held but the department is committed to the continued development of initiatives to ensure employees can support customers who may be suffering from a mental health condition.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","64631","2017-03-03T15:03:14.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692006/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692006/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692006/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Administration of Justice: Mental Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what training is provided to (a) court staff and (b) members of the judiciary on identifying and supporting court users with a mental health condition.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bingham","High Peak","Andrew Bingham","64632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692007","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>The role of the Commissioner for Victims and Witnesses is defined in the Domestic Violence, Crime and Victims Act 2004. It is to promote the interests of victims and witnesses, encourage good practice in their treatment, and regularly review the operation of the Code of Practice for Victims. There are no current plans to change the role of the Commissioner as provided by the legislation.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-02-28T16:25:56.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692007/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692007/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692007/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Victims' Commissioner","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether she has plans to increase or strengthen the powers and duties of the Victims' Commissioner.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","64618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692008","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-27","<p>We have made positive steps to improve the experience of victims, to reduce unnecessary stress and lessen the emotional turmoil of attending court. But we have been clear that more must be done. That is why we will set out our strategy for victims within 12 months, including bringing forward any appropriate legislation.</p><p> </p><p>We are actively considering how compliance with the Code of Practice for Victims of Crime (Victims’ Code) might be improved and monitored. We are also exploring how those responsible for delivery of rights and entitlements might be better held accountable for any failings.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","64620","2017-02-27T16:39:59.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692008/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692008/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692008/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Crime: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether she plans to collect evidence on the effectiveness of the Code of Practice for Victims of Crime.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","64619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692009","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-23","<p>To begin the process of reviewing the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012 (LASPO), the Government plans to submit a Post Legislative Memorandum to the Justice Select Committee in a few months’ time. We will outline our plans for the post-implementation review (PIR) of LASPO in more detail when we submit the memorandum to Parliament. The PIR will cover the reforms to legal aid made by LASPO. We intend to work closely with key parties across the sector to inform the review’s conclusions.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","64634 ; 64689","2017-02-23T16:57:58.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692009/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692009/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692009/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whom her Department plans to consult during the development of the review into the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012.","false","Biography information for Anne McLaughlin","Glasgow North East","Anne McLaughlin","64633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692010","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-27","<p>The Attorney General and Justice Secretary are looking at how section 41 of the Youth Justice and Criminal Evidence Act 1999 is working in practice. This includes examining the original policy intent of the legislation, its implementation and how it is currently operating.</p><p> </p><p>This work is being led by officials in the Ministry of Justice and Attorney General’s Office who are seeking views from the judiciary, practitioners and victims’ groups.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-02-27T16:47:26.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692010/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692010/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692010/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Rape: Trials","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether her Department plans to review how section 41 of the Youth Justice and Criminal Evidence Act 1999 is working.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","64670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692011","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-23","<p>The Ministry of Justice has not assessed the effectiveness of the National Grid Young Offenders Programme in reducing reoffending rates.</p><p> </p><p>In our Employment Strategy, which will be published later this year, we will outline our plans to support prisoners in gaining the skills and experience they need to prepare them for employment in modern jobs on release. As part of this, we will be engaging with a wide variety of stakeholders, including the National Grid Young Offenders Programme.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-02-23T17:55:22.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692011/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692011/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692011/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Young Offenders: Rehabilitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment she has made of the effectiveness of the National Grid Young Offenders Programme in reducing reoffending rates.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","64693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692012","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-23","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-02-23T17:00:13.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692012/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692012/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692012/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Administration of Justice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many cases were dropped by courts in England and Wales due to the (a) ill-health, (b) old age and (c) youth of the defendants in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","64696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692013","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-19","<p>Data is collected in respect of participation and achievement in Level 2 English courses (equivalent to GCSE standard). These can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/576930/feandskills-OLASS-participation-and-achievement.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/576930/feandskills-OLASS-participation-and-achievement.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>These data refer to English courses funded by the Offender Learning and Skills Service (OLASS) in English prisons. Historically, data specific to the completion of GCSE English courses is not collected. In Wales responsibility for learning and skills in prisons is devolved to the Welsh Government and this specific data breakdown is not routinely held centrally, but is held locally at specific sites.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-04-19T10:32:04.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692013/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692013/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692013/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Prisoners: GCSE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of prisoners completed GCSE English courses in the last (a) year, (b) two years and (c) five years.","false","Biography information for Susan Elan Jones","Clwyd South","Susan Elan Jones","64656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692014","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-23","<p>To begin the process of reviewing the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012 (LASPO), the Government plans to submit a Post Legislative Memorandum to the Justice Select Committee in a few months’ time. We will outline our plans for the post-implementation review (PIR) of LASPO in more detail when we submit the memorandum to Parliament. The PIR will cover the reforms to legal aid made by LASPO. We intend to work closely with key parties across the sector to inform the review’s conclusions.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","64633 ; 64634","2017-02-23T16:57:58.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692014/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692014/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692014/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether the review into the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012 will include an open call for evidence.","false","Biography information for Anne McLaughlin","Glasgow North East","Anne McLaughlin","64689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692015","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>There has been no direct Departmental spend with Uber through either a contract or by using a GPC card.</p><p>There is the possibility of individual usage which may have been claimed through expenses, but expenses data is not held below the level of “taxi fare” as a generic classification making it impossible to extract such data.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-02-28T16:17:46.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692015/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692015/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692015/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Ministry of Justice: Uber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much her Department has spent on (a) Uber for Business and (b) other Uber transactions since 28 October 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","64380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692016","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>The table below shows the number and contract value of contracts let by MoJ since Financial Year 2010/11.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Count of Total Con/Fwork Val (£)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Sum of Total Con/Fwork Val (£)2</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>161</p></td><td><p>£6,389,363,484</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>578</p></td><td><p>£1,883,462,647</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>600</p></td><td><p>£3,399,238,346</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>579</p></td><td><p>£994,022,004</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>626</p></td><td><p>£9,210,984,689</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>353</p></td><td><p>£671,933,056</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Grand Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2897</strong></p></td><td><p><strong> £22,549,004,226</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The information requested relating to the value of pro bono costs and the number of work days contracted out in each such year is not held centrally.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-02-28T16:19:48.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692016/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692016/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692016/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Ministry of Justice: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the total (a) number and (b) value of Government contracts that have been contracted out by her Department was in each year since 2010; what the value of pro bono costs was in each such year; and what estimate she has made of the number of work days contracted out in each such year.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","64398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692017","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-24","<p>Data on releases and reasons for recall are currently published, broken down by gender, for the period 1 January 2015 to 30 September 2016 in Offender Management Statistics Quarterly (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/offender-management-statistics-quarterly" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/offender-management-statistics-quarterly</a> ).</p><p>Before 2015, only one reason could be recorded against each recall. Therefore, to provide the data requested, we would have manually to check each record to identify if there were further charges; this would incur disproportionate costs.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-24T12:29:24.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692017/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692017/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692017/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Prisoners' Release: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the number of women released and subsequently returned to custody following a technical breach of a supervision condition, excluding those returned for the commission of a further offence, was in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","64438"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692018","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-06","<p>The Victims’ Code is freely available online, but we know more must be done to support and protect victims. We have made positive steps to improve the experience of victims, by reducing unnecessary stress and emotional turmoil of attending court. We have also reconvened the Victims’ Panel, so we can learn from the experiences of victims of crime.</p><p> </p><p>Under the Victims’ Code those victims who feel that their rights have not been met can complain directly to the criminal justice agency concerned, and if they remain dissatisfied can take their complaint to the Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman. We are currently considering how compliance with the Victims’ Code might be improved and monitored, and exploring how those delivering services can be better held to account. Plans to engage with and obtain the views of victims and victims’ groups and criminal justice agencies are being developed. We will set out our strategy for victims within 12 months, and will bring forward any appropriate primary legislation.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","64646","2017-03-06T15:59:15.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692018/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692018/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692018/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Crime: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps her Department takes to ensure that victims of crime are made aware of the existence of the Victims' Code.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","64533"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692019","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>The information requested is not held centrally. We are determined to improve the family justice response to stalking and domestic abuse and are legislating to prevent abusers from questioning their victims in person in family proceedings.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-02-28T17:24:51.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692019/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692019/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692019/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Offenders: Crimes against the Person","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate she has made of the number of vexatious applications taken out against their victim by a person convicted of (a) stalking or (b) domestic abuse in the family or civil courts in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","64525"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692020","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-02-28T17:22:40.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692020/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692020/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692020/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Domestic Abuse: Convictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) men and (b) women were convicted of domestic abuse-related crimes in each of the last three years; and how many in each category received a custodial sentence.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","64524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692021","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-24","<p>We, and other Departments, are working closely with the Department for Exiting the European Union on all aspects of exiting the European Union.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-02-24T14:34:09.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692021/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692021/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692021/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Ministry of Justice: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what discussions she has had with the Department for Exiting the European Union on the contents of the White Paper entitled The United Kingdom's exit from and new partnership with the European Union, Cm 9417, published in February 2017.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","64549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692023","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>Over the last three years the Ministry of Justice has had and continues to have due regard, as necessary, to the public sector equality duty in exercising its functions. The Equality Act does not require this due regard to take the form of an equality impact assessment, nor does it define an equality impact assessment, and the department does not maintain a record of such assessments.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-02-28T16:21:45.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692023/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692023/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692023/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Ministry of Justice: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many equality impact assessments have been carried out in the last three years on public service reforms which impact on (a) departmental staff and (b) members of the public; and if she will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","64448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692024","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-24","<p>One year proven reoffending rates for the first cohort managed under our probation reforms will be published in the quarterly proven reoffending statistics bulletin in October 2017, which will be available on <a href="http://gov.uk" target="_blank">gov.uk</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Interim Payment by Results figures, based on a shorter reoffending period than the final results, were published on 27 October 2016 and 26 January 2017. These can be found on GOV.uk.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-24T13:08:51.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692024/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692024/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692024/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Reoffenders: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what trends there have been in reoffending rates in London since the reform of the probation service and the introduction of community rehabilitation companies.","false","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","64502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692025","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>The information requested is available in the criminal justice systems quarterly statistics on GOV.UK.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-28T16:32:37.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692025/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692025/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692025/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Stalking: Convictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people were convicted of stalking offences under section 4A of the Protection from Harassment Act 1997 in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","64486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692026","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-02-28T17:20:55.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692026/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692026/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692026/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-20","Rape: Trials","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many applications have been made to Crown Courts in England and Wales under section 41 of the Youth Justice and Criminal Evidence Act 1999 in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","64487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692027","Leader of the House","false","2017-02-27","<p>The Office of the Leader of the House of Commons is an integral part of the Cabinet Office.<br><br>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given to him by my right hon. Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office on 27 February 2017, to Question UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-02-20/64401/" target="_blank">64401</a>.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2017-02-27T17:37:34.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692027/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692027/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692027/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2017-02-20","Leader of the House of Commons: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what the total (a) number and (b) value of Government contracts that have been contracted out by his Office was in each year since 2010; what the value of pro bono costs was in each such year; and what estimate he has made of the number of work days contracted out in each such year.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","64399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692028","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-02-28","<p>The total number and value of Government Contracts that have been awarded by the Northern Ireland Office since 2010 is shown below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>No. of Contracts</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Value of Contracts, £’000s</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>90</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>5,760</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>3,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2017</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The Department does not hold any information on which of these involved contracting out, pro bono costs or the number of work days contracted out to enable me to provide an answer for the remainder of your question.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-02-28T11:47:02.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692028/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692028/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692028/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-02-20","Northern Ireland Office: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what the total (a) number and (b) value of Government contracts that have been contracted out by his Department was in each year since 2010; what the value of pro bono costs was in each such year; and what estimate he has made of the number of work days contracted out in each such year.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","64400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692029","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-02-23","<p>Under the provisions of the Political Parties, Elections and Referendums Act 2000, the Electoral Commission are responsible for publishing details of spending by registered campaigners, including in relation to the recent EU referendum. I have no role in publishing information relating to campaign expenditure.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-02-23T12:55:09.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692029/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692029/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692029/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-02-20","Political Parties: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if he will publish the breakdown of spending by registered parties in Northern Ireland during the EU referendum campaign recorded by the Northern Ireland Electoral Commission.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","64363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692030","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-02-23","<p>I am keen to see progress on this issue and have written to the NI political parties seeking their views on moving to full transparency. I am currently considering responses from the parties before deciding on next steps. In line with usual pre-election protocols I will not be making any announcements until after the forthcoming Assembly election.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-02-23T12:53:20.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692030/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692030/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692030/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-02-20","Political Parties: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to make public donation information recorded in the Northern Ireland Electoral Commission's donor register from 2014 onwards required under the Northern Ireland Miscellaneous Provisions Act 2014; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","64521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692031","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-02-27","<p>The Northern Ireland Office considers equality issues in exercising its functions, to comply with all relevant equality legislation and to ensure it understands how its activities will affect different people. Although there is no legal requirement to publish equality impact assessments under the public sector equality duty at Section 149 of the Equality Act 2010, the Department must also comply with the requirements of Section 75 of the Northern Ireland Act 1998.</p><p> </p><p>In accordance with Schedule 9 4.(2)(d) of the Northern Ireland Act 1998, the Department is required to publish details of all policy screenings or Equality Impact Assessments (EQIAs) on a six monthly basis and include a summary of all screening reports and EQIAs in its Section 75 Annual Progress Report. The latest reports can be found on the Northern Ireland Office website at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=northern-ireland-office&amp;page=2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=northern-ireland-office&amp;page=2</a></p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-02-27T13:10:20.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692031/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692031/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692031/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-02-20","Northern Ireland Office: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many equality impact assessments have been carried out in the last three years on public service reforms which impact on (a) departmental staff and (b) members of the public; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","64449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692032","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-02-27","<p>I and my officials have regular discussions with colleagues at the Department for Exiting the European Union on the impacts and opportunities for Northern Ireland arising from the decision to exit the European Union.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-02-27T13:11:42.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692032/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692032/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692032/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-02-20","Northern Ireland Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions he has had with the Department for Exiting the European Union on the contents of the White Paper entitled The United Kingdom's exit from and new partnership with the European Union, Cm 9417, published in February 2017.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","64550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692033","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-02-23","<p>The Northern Ireland Office operates in line with Ministry of Justice recruitment policies and we are supportive of the Ban the Box initiative.</p><p>No employees in the Department currently have unspent convictions.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-02-23T15:29:47.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692033/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692033/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692033/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-02-20","Northern Ireland Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether his Department operates a ban the box employment policy in respect of ex-offender job applicants with unspent convictions; and how many employees of his Department have unspent convictions.","false","Biography information for Andrew Selous","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","64478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692034","Cabinet Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office and is included in this reply.</p><p>Following a check of Cabinet Office records, information on spend on (a) Uber for Business and (b) other Uber transactions since October 2016 is not held centrally.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","64368","2017-02-24T11:55:00.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692034/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692034/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692034/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-02-20","Prime Minister: Uber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much 10 Downing Street has spent on (a) Uber for Business and (b) other Uber transactions since 28 October 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","64381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692035","Cabinet Office","false","2017-02-27","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office and is included in this reply.</p><p>Since January 2011, details of central government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive</a></p><p>Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a></p><p>Details of contracts under £10,000 awarded by Cabinet Office as well as the total value of pro bono costs and the number of work days contracted out are not held centrally.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2017-02-27T15:32:16.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692035/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692035/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692035/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-02-20","Prime Minister: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the total (a) number and (b) value of Government contracts that have been contracted out by 10 Downing Street was in each year since 2010; what the value of pro bono costs was in each such year; and what estimate he has made of the number of work days contracted out in each such year.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","64401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692036","Prime Minister","false","2017-02-23","<p>The Social Reform Cabinet Committee oversees and agrees social policy reforms and leads the Government’s work to increase social mobility, deliver social justice and make the UK a country that works for everyone.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-02-23T14:02:23.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692036/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692036/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692036/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-02-20","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what steps the Social Reform Cabinet Committee has taken to reduce child poverty.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","64687"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692037","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-23","<p>​The Prime Minister spoke to President Trump on 14 February, as part of their regular engagement. They discussed a range of issues, including the President's State Visit to the UK. Neither the precise timing nor the content have been agreed.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-02-23T17:14:56.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692037/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692037/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692037/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-20","State Visits: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the US administration on a State visit to the UK by President Trump since the Prime Minister issued the official invitation.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","64697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692038","Scotland Office","false","2017-02-28","<p>Other than minor or bespoke purchases, the Scotland Office does not normally undertake direct procurement or tendering projects. It uses existing service contracts between suppliers and the Scottish Government or the Ministry of Justice.</p><p> </p><p>Since May 2010, only one contract has been contracted out by the Scotland Office. This was issued to the Royal Mail in 2011-12 for its role in providing candidates' free mailing in the Scottish Parliament election of 2011, the value of which was just over £6.4 million.</p><p> </p><p>We do not record information on pro bono costs nor the number of work days contracted out each year.</p><p> </p><p>Since January 2011, central government departments have been required to publish details of contracts above the value of £10,000 on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive" target="_blank"><strong>https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive</strong></a></p><p> </p><p>Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank"><strong>https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</strong></a></p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-02-28T15:16:36.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692038/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692038/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692038/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-02-20","Scotland Office: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what the total (a) number and (b) value of Government contracts that have been contracted out by his Department was in each year since 2010; what the value of pro bono costs was in each such year; and what estimate he has made of the number of work days contracted out in each such year.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","64402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692039","Scotland Office","false","2017-02-28","<p>The Scotland Office do not centrally record information on (a) Uber for Business or (b) other Uber transactions.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-02-28T15:14:34.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692039/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692039/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692039/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-02-20","Scotland Office: Uber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how much his Department has spent on (a) Uber for Business and (b) other Uber transactions since 28 October 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","64382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692040","Scotland Office","false","2017-02-23","<p>The Scotland Office does not employ staff directly. These matters would be for the employing departments.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-02-23T15:22:47.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692040/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692040/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692040/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-02-20","Scotland Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether his Department operates a ban the box employment policy in respect of ex-offender job applicants with unspent convictions; and how many employees of his Department have unspent convictions.","false","Biography information for Andrew Selous","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","64479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692041","Scotland Office","false","2017-02-27","<p>The Scotland Office, and other Departments, are working closely with the Department for Exiting the European Union on all aspects of exiting the European Union. I have regular discussions with the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union on matters relating to the UK’s Exit. In addition, the White Paper was the subject of discussion with the devolved administrations at the Joint Ministerial Committee on EU Negotiations on 8 February. The third chapter of this White Paper explains how, as we leave the EU, we will aim to strengthen the union between the four nations of the United Kingdom. To this end we are working to ensure we get the best possible deal for the whole of the UK.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-02-27T13:15:12.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692041/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692041/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692041/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-02-20","Scotland Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with the Department for Exiting the European Union on the contents of the White Paper entitled The United Kingdom's exit from and new partnership with the European Union, Cm 9417, published in February 2017.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","64551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692042","Scotland Office","false","2017-02-27","<p>Over the last three years the Scotland Office has had and continues to have due regard, as necessary, to the public sector equality duty in exercising its functions. The Equality Act does not require this due regard to take the form of an equality impact assessment, nor does it define an equality impact assessment, and the Scotland Office does not maintain a record of such assessments.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-02-27T13:16:22.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692042/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692042/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692042/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-02-20","Scotland Office: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many equality impact assessments have been carried out in the last three years on public service reforms which impact on (a) departmental staff and (b) members of the public; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","64450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692043","Department for Transport","false","2017-02-27","<p>It is for individual local authorities to decide whether to subsidise bus services that are not commercially viable but which they consider socially necessary, balancing this need against their other funding priorities.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-02-27T14:40:27.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692043/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692043/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692043/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-02-20","Bus Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make it his policy to protect local bus services when such services are discontinued by private bus companies due to concerns over profitability.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","64431"
